Florida is getting national attention for its housing market explosion and lack of affordability. A recent report from Realtor.com found that the Tampa Bay metro area had one of the largest year-over-year rent increases in the country from February 2021 to February 2022. The region also had one of the highest percentages of people spending more than 30 percent of their income on housing. As advocacy groups call for rent stabilization and local governments vow to designate funds to build more affordable housing, longtime residents face eviction. Below is a list of resources to turn to if you are or someone you know are at risk of losing your housing. The services offered range from legal counsel to rental assistance, and food and healthcare providers. Representatives from the agencies said it is important to get in touch as early as possible if you fear falling behind on rent or need assistance. Hillsborough County Resources ***** Tampa Hillsborough Homeless Initiative About: A searchable database of services ranging from food programs and emergency shelters, to employment assistance and health services. Website: https://unity.myresourcedirectory.com/ Phone: 813-223-6115 ***** Hillsborough County Community Resource Centers About: Five centers located across Hillsborough County that provide guidance and resources to community members, including assistance with housing. Website: https://www.hillsboroughcounty.org/en/residents/social-services/financial-assistance/find-a-community-resource-center Phone: (813) 272-5220 ***** Hillsborough County Emergency Rental Assistance Program About: Provides approved households with assistance for rent and electric bills. Website: https://www.hillsboroughcounty.org/en/residents/public-safety/covid-19-financial-assistance/r3-program Phone: (866) 375-9114 ***** Hillsborough County Affordable Housing Services About: Assists low-income families with affordable housing opportunities. Website: https://www.hillsboroughcounty.org/en/government/departments/affordable-housing Phone: (813)246-3150 ***** Bay Area Legal Services About: Provides free legal services and online tenant tip sheets to residents people in the Tampa Bay region who need help with housing law. Website: https://bals.org/help/housing Phone: 800-625-2257 ***** Gulfcoast Legal Services About: Offers legal assistance to low-income residents in the greater Tampa Bay area. Website: https://gulfcoastlegal.org/housing-stability-assistance Phone: 727-821-0726 Pinellas County Resources ***** Homeless Leadership Alliance of Pinellas About: Strives to prevent homelessness in Pinellas County through a county-wide crisis response system. Website: https://www.pinellashomeless.org/resources Phone: 727-582-7916 OR call 2-1-1 for the homeless helpline. ***** Pinellas County Emergency Assistance Programs About: A list of resources kept by the county, including emergency rent relief programs. Website: https://covid19.pinellascounty.org/where-to-get-help/ Phone: 727-464-3000 OR call 2-1-1 for the homeless helpline. ***** Pinellas County Housing Authority About: Provides Housing to qualifying individuals and families, but long wait lists apply. Website: https://www.pinellashousing.com/ Phone: 727-443-7684 ***** Pinellas County Resources for Renters About: A tip sheet to inform renters about legal rights. Website: https://rent.pinellas.gov/ ***** Pinellas Community Law Program About: Provides free legal services to Pinellas County residents, including landlord-tenant legal counsel, and an eviction diversion program. Website: https://lawprogram.org/ Phone: 727-582-7480 ***** Bay Area Legal Services About: Provides free legal services and online tenant tip sheets to residents people in the Tampa Bay region who need help with housing law. Website: https://bals.org/help/housing Phone: 800-625-2257 ***** Gulfcoast Legal Services About: Offers legal assistance to low-income residents in the greater Tampa Bay area. Website: https://gulfcoastlegal.org/housing-stability-assistance Phone: 727-821-0726 ***** St. Petersburg Tenants Union About: A politically active tenants rights organization based in St. Petersburg that mobilizes for rent control and advocates for people struggling to afford housing. Website: https://www.stpetersburgtenantsunion.org/ Contact Email: SPTenantsUnion@gmail.com Pasco County Resources ***** Pasco Homeless Coalition About: More than 40 organizations working together to provide help to people facing homelessness or at risk of facing homelessness. Website: https://www.pascohomelesscoalition.org/ Phone: 727-842-8605 ***** Pasco County Rental Assistance Program About: Provides assistance to renters with funds distributed by the U.S. Treasury to Pasco County. Website: https://www.pascocountyfl.net/4385/Pasco-HEART-20 Phone: 727-834-3447 ***** Pasco County Housing Authority About: Assists low-income families with affordable housing opportunities. Website: https://pascocountyhousing.org/ Phone: (352) 567-0848 ***** Bay Area Legal Services About: Provides free legal services and online tenant tip sheets to residents people in the Tampa Bay region who need help with housing law. Website: https://bals.org/help/housing Phone: 800-625-2257 Additional Services: ***** 211 Tampa Bay Cares About: Assistance with food, health care and housing resources across Tampa Bay. Website: https://211tampabay.org/ Phone: 727-210-4211 OR Call 2-1-1 ***** Feeding Tampa Bay About: A food pantry network serving 10 counties around Tampa Bay. Website: https://feedingtampabay.org/ways-we-serve Phone: 813-254-1190 ***** Catholic Charities About: Assists people, regardless of faith, who are struggling with poverty through local service chapters. Website: https://www.catholiccharitiesusa.org/our-vision-and-ministry/ Phone: 703-549-1390 ***** Florida Housing Coalition Housing Search About: A free, state resource for renters and property managers in Florida to help find housing that fits individual needs and income levels. Website: https://fl